**Idea:**

Any contiguous subarray sum from index j+1j+1j+1 to index iii can be written in terms of prefix sums. Define a prefix sum array

P[i]=a1+a2+⋯+ai,with&nbsp;P[0]=0.P[i] = a_1 + a_2 + \cdots + a_i,\quad \text{with } P[0] = 0.P[i]=a1​+a2​+⋯+ai​,with&nbsp;P[0]=0.Then, the sum of the subarray starting at index j+1j+1j+1 and ending at iii is

P[i]−P[j].P[i] - P[j].P[i]−P[j].Since we require that the subarray has at least KKK elements, the starting index jjj must satisfy

i−j≥Korj≤i−K.i - j \ge K \quad \text{or} \quad j \le i - K.i−j≥Korj≤i−K.Thus, for each ending index iii (with i≥Ki\ge Ki≥K), the maximum sum for a segment ending at iii is obtained by subtracting the minimum prefix among P[0],P[1],…,P[i−K]P[0], P[1], \ldots, P[i-K]P[0],P[1],…,P[i−K], i.e.,

candidate=P[i]−min⁡0≤j≤i−KP[j].\text{candidate} = P[i] - \min_{0 \le j \le i-K} P[j].candidate=P[i]−0≤j≤i−Kmin​P[j].We can precompute the prefix sums and also maintain an array of minimum prefix sums. The maximum of all these candidates gives the final answer.

**Time Complexity:** O(N)O(N)O(N), where NNN is the number of stations.

**C++ Code for Approach 1:**

`#include &lt;iostream&gt;
#include &lt;vector&gt;
#include &lt;algorithm&gt;
using namespace std;

int main(){
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(nullptr);

    int N, K;
    cin &gt;&gt; N &gt;&gt; K;

    vector&lt;long long&gt; arr(N);
    for (int i = 0; i &lt; N; i++){
        cin &gt;&gt; arr[i];
    }

    // Compute prefix sums: prefix[i] = sum of first i elements.
    vector&lt;long long&gt; prefix(N+1, 0);
    for (int i = 1; i &lt;= N; i++){
        prefix[i] = prefix[i-1] + arr[i-1];
    }

    // Precompute minimum prefix sums: minPrefix[i] = minimum prefix among prefix[0] to prefix[i]
    vector&lt;long long&gt; minPrefix(N+1, 0);
    minPrefix[0] = prefix[0];
    for (int i = 1; i &lt;= N; i++){
        minPrefix[i] = min(minPrefix[i-1], prefix[i]);
    }

    // Calculate the maximum profit for segments of at least K stations.
    long long ans = -1000000000000000000LL; // Initialize with a very small number.
    for (int i = K; i &lt;= N; i++){
        ans = max(ans, prefix[i] - minPrefix[i - K]);
    }

    cout &lt;&lt; ans &lt;&lt; "\n";
    return 0;
}
