`**Idea:**

Another way to solve the problem is to break it into two parts:



**Fixed Window of Size KKK:**

First, compute the sum of every contiguous segment of exactly KKK stations. This gives us a base profit for that window.




**Extend the Window:**

In some cases, extending the window (adding stations before the fixed window) may result in a higher profit. To decide whether to extend, we compute the maximum subarray sum ending at the station just before the current window using Kadane’s algorithm.



Let’s define:


`window_sum` as the sum of the last KKK elements in the current window.
`best[i]` as the maximum subarray sum ending at index iii (computed via Kadane’s algorithm).
Then, for a window ending at index iii (where i≥K−1i \ge K-1i≥K−1), the candidate sum is:

candidate=window_sum+max⁡(0,best[i−K]).\text{candidate} = \text{window\_sum} + \max(0, \text{best}[i-K]).candidate=window_sum+max(0,best[i−K]).This means we add the best extension from before the window if it is positive. We then track the maximum candidate among all windows.

**Time Complexity:** O(N)O(N)O(N), with NNN being the size of the array.

**C++ Code for Approach 2:**

`#include &lt;iostream&gt;
#include &lt;vector&gt;
#include &lt;algorithm&gt;
using namespace std;

int main(){
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(nullptr);

    int N, K;
    cin &gt;&gt; N &gt;&gt; K;

    vector&lt;long long&gt; a(N);
    for (int i = 0; i &lt; N; i++){
        cin &gt;&gt; a[i];
    }

    // Compute maximum subarray sum ending at each index (Kadane's algorithm).
    vector&lt;long long&gt; best(N, 0);
    best[0] = a[0];
    for (int i = 1; i &lt; N; i++){
        best[i] = max(a[i], best[i-1] + a[i]);
    }

    // Calculate initial window sum for the first K elements.
    long long windowSum = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i &lt; K; i++){
        windowSum += a[i];
    }

    long long ans = windowSum;
    // Slide the window from index K to N-1.
    for (int i = K; i &lt; N; i++){
        windowSum += a[i] - a[i - K];
        long long candidate = windowSum;
        if (i - K &gt;= 0)
            candidate += max(0LL, best[i - K]);
        ans = max(ans, candidate);
    }

    cout &lt;&lt; ans &lt;&lt; "\n";
    return 0;
}
